{
  "video_id": "AEKy1AS75Zs",
  "title": "Why I fight for the education of refugee girls (like me) | Mary Maker",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12962.0,
      "end_time": 15928.0,
      "text": "We do not choose where to be born."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17700.0,
      "end_time": 20215.0,
      "text": "We do not choose who our parents are."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21264.0,
      "end_time": 25499.0,
      "text": "But we do choose how we are going to live our lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 26810.0,
      "end_time": 29526.0,
      "text": "I did not choose to be born in South Sudan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 29551.0,
      "end_time": 31686.0,
      "text": "a country rife with conflict."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32511.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34534.00000000001,
      "text": "I did not choose my name --"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 35304.0,
      "end_time": 36842.0,
      "text": "Nyiriak,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36866.0,
      "end_time": 38348.0,
      "text": "which means \"war.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39308.0,
      "end_time": 41271.0,
      "text": "I've always rejected it"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41295.0,
      "end_time": 44730.0,
      "text": "and all the legacy it was born into."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44754.0,
      "end_time": 46973.0,
      "text": "I choose to be called Mary."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48154.0,
      "end_time": 51837.0,
      "text": "As a teacher, I've stood in front of 120 students,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51861.0,
      "end_time": 54860.0,
      "text": "so this stage does not intimidate me."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 55996.0,
      "end_time": 59545.0,
      "text": "My students come from war-torn countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 60101.0,
      "end_time": 62638.0,
      "text": "They're so different from each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 62662.0,
      "end_time": 65480.0,
      "text": "but they have one thing in common:"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 65504.00000000001,
      "end_time": 69369.0,
      "text": "they fled their homes in order to stay alive."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 70616.0,
      "end_time": 74127.0,
      "text": "Some of them belong to parents back home in South Sudan"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 74151.0,
      "end_time": 75473.0,
      "text": "who are killing each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 75497.0,
      "end_time": 79947.0,
      "text": "because they belong to a different tribe or they have a different belief."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 80922.0,
      "end_time": 85209.0,
      "text": "Others come from other African countries devastated by war."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 85823.0,
      "end_time": 88857.0,
      "text": "But when they enter my class, they make friends,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 88882.0,
      "end_time": 90519.0,
      "text": "they walk home together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 91149.0,
      "end_time": 93500.0,
      "text": "they do their homework together."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 93711.0,
      "end_time": 96739.0,
      "text": "There is no hatred allowed in my class."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 98780.0,
      "end_time": 102211.0,
      "text": "My story is like that of so many other refugees."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 103630.0,
      "end_time": 105137.0,
      "text": "The war came when I was still a baby."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 106131.0,
      "end_time": 107348.0,
      "text": "And my father,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 107372.0,
      "end_time": 110227.0,
      "text": "who had been absent in most of my early childhood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 110251.0,
      "end_time": 112827.0,
      "text": "was doing what other men were doing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 112851.0,
      "end_time": 114578.0,
      "text": "fighting for the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 115283.0,
      "end_time": 118403.0,
      "text": "He had two wives and many children."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 120459.0,
      "end_time": 122788.0,
      "text": "My mother was his second wife,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 122812.0,
      "end_time": 125910.0,
      "text": "married to him at the age of 16."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 125588.0,
      "end_time": 129609.0,
      "text": "This is simply because my mother came from a poor background,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 130279.0,
      "end_time": 132790.0,
      "text": "and she had no choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 132103.0,
      "end_time": 135450.0,
      "text": "My father, on the other hand, was rich."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 135690.0,
      "end_time": 136402.0,
      "text": "He had many cows."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 138987.0,
      "end_time": 142174.0,
      "text": "Gunshots were the order of the day."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 144713.0,
      "end_time": 147605.0,
      "text": "My community was constantly under attack."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 148526.0,
      "end_time": 153166.0,
      "text": "Communities would fight each other as they took water along the Nile."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 153190.0,
      "end_time": 154482.0,
      "text": "But that was not all."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 155257.0,
      "end_time": 159161.0,
      "text": "Planes would drop the spinning and terrifying bombs"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 159185.0,
      "end_time": 161411.0,
      "text": "that chopped off people's limbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 161435.0,
      "end_time": 164711.0,
      "text": "But the most terrifying thing for every single parent"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 164735.0,
      "end_time": 170949.0,
      "text": "was to see their children being abducted and turned into young soldiers."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 171877.0,
      "end_time": 174198.0,
      "text": "My mother dug a trench"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 174222.0,
      "end_time": 176371.0,
      "text": "that soon became our home."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 177150.0,
      "end_time": 179503.0,
      "text": "But yet, we did not feel protected."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 180455.0,
      "end_time": 184405.0,
      "text": "She had to flee in search of a safe place for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 184429.0,
      "end_time": 187851.0,
      "text": "I was four years old, and my younger sister was two."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 189267.0,
      "end_time": 191280.0,
      "text": "We joined a huge mass of people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 191304.0,
      "end_time": 195220.0,
      "text": "and together we walked for many agonizing days"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 195244.0,
      "end_time": 197166.0,
      "text": "in search of a secure place."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 197190.0,
      "end_time": 198863.0,
      "text": "But we could barely rest"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 199954.0,
      "end_time": 202863.0,
      "text": "before we were attacked again."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 204159.0,
      "end_time": 206602.0,
      "text": "I remember my mother was pregnant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 206627.0,
      "end_time": 209678.0,
      "text": "when she would take turns to carry me and my younger sister."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 210362.0,
      "end_time": 213236.0,
      "text": "We finally made it across the Kenyan border, yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 213887.0,
      "end_time": 219340.0,
      "text": "But that was the longest journey that I have ever had in my whole life."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 220280.0,
      "end_time": 223551.0,
      "text": "My feet were raw with blisters."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 225630.0,
      "end_time": 227186.0,
      "text": "To our surprise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 227210.0,
      "end_time": 230521.0,
      "text": "we found other family members who had fled into the camp earlier on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 230545.0,
      "end_time": 232212.0,
      "text": "where you all are today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 232236.0,
      "end_time": 233941.0,
      "text": "the Kakuma camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 233966.0,
      "end_time": 237646.0,
      "text": "Now, I want you all to be very quiet just for a moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 240574.0,
      "end_time": 242153.0,
      "text": "Do you hear that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 244220.0,
      "end_time": 247206.0,
      "text": "The sound of silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 248268.0,
      "end_time": 249642.0,
      "text": "No gunshots."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 251157.0,
      "end_time": 253500.0,
      "text": "Peace, at last."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 254279.0,
      "end_time": 257733.0,
      "text": "That was my first memory of this camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 259154.0,
      "end_time": 261507.0,
      "text": "When you move from a war zone"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 261531.0,
      "end_time": 264540.0,
      "text": "and come to a secure place like Kakuma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 264780.0,
      "end_time": 265529.0,
      "text": "you've really gone far."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 267655.0,
      "end_time": 270556.0,
      "text": "I only stayed in the camp for three years, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 270580.0,
      "end_time": 273644.0,
      "text": "My father, who had been absent in most of my early childhood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 273668.0,
      "end_time": 275550.0,
      "text": "came back into my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 275697.0,
      "end_time": 279860.0,
      "text": "And he organized for me to move with my uncle"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 279110.0,
      "end_time": 280670.0,
      "text": "to our family in Nakuru."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 281328.0,
      "end_time": 283770.0,
      "text": "There, I found my father's first wife,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 283795.0,
      "end_time": 287376.0,
      "text": "my half sisters and my half brothers."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 287400.0,
      "end_time": 289479.0,
      "text": "I got enrolled in school."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 289503.0,
      "end_time": 294800.0,
      "text": "I remember my first day in school -- I could sing and laugh again --"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 294105.0,
      "end_time": 297403.0,
      "text": "and my first set of school uniforms, you bet."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 298317.0,
      "end_time": 299678.0,
      "text": "It was amazing."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 301360.0,
      "end_time": 303765.0,
      "text": "But then I came to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 304622.0,
      "end_time": 308884.0,
      "text": "that my uncle did not find it fit for me to go to school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 310194.0,
      "end_time": 312873.0,
      "text": "simply because I was a girl."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 314649.0,
      "end_time": 317590.0,
      "text": "My half brothers were his first priority."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 318622.0,
      "end_time": 322383.0,
      "text": "He would say, \"Educating a girl is a waste of time.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 322773.0,
      "end_time": 327734.0,
      "text": "And for that reason, I missed many days of school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 327758.0,
      "end_time": 329734.0,
      "text": "because the fees were not paid."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 331364.0,
      "end_time": 333280.0,
      "text": "My father stepped in"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 333305.0,
      "end_time": 336428.0,
      "text": "and organized for me to go to boarding school."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 337253.0,
      "end_time": 341313.0,
      "text": "I remember the faith that he put in me over the couple of years to come."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 341337.0,
      "end_time": 347000.0,
      "text": "He would say, \"Education is an animal that you have to overcome."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 347779.0,
      "end_time": 351101.0,
      "text": "With an education, you can survive."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 351838.0,
      "end_time": 355924.0,
      "text": "Education shall be your first husband.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 356557.0,
      "end_time": 361633.0,
      "text": "And with these words came in his first big investment."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 361657.0,
      "end_time": 362931.0,
      "text": "I felt lucky!"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 363627.0,
      "end_time": 366806.0,
      "text": "But I was missing something:"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 368462.0,
      "end_time": 369613.0,
      "text": "my mother."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 371640.0,
      "end_time": 373555.0,
      "text": "My mother had been left behind in the camp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 374511.0,
      "end_time": 377240.0,
      "text": "and I had not seen her since I left it."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 378197.0,
      "end_time": 382816.0,
      "text": "Six years without seeing her was really long."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 384245.0,
      "end_time": 385488.0,
      "text": "I was alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 386178.0,
      "end_time": 387417.0,
      "text": "in school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 388117.0,
      "end_time": 389735.0,
      "text": "when I heard of her death."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 392128.0,
      "end_time": 394704.0,
      "text": "I've seen many people back in South Sudan"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 396316.0,
      "end_time": 397977.0,
      "text": "lose their lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 398100.0,
      "end_time": 399924.0,
      "text": "I've heard from neighbors"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 399948.0,
      "end_time": 402424.0,
      "text": "lose their sons, their husbands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 403159.0,
      "end_time": 404435.0,
      "text": "their children."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 405104.0,
      "end_time": 408573.0,
      "text": "But I never thought that that would ever come into my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 409840.0,
      "end_time": 413395.0,
      "text": "A month earlier, my stepmother,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 413420.0,
      "end_time": 417439.0,
      "text": "who had been so good to me back in Nakuru, died first."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 419764.0,
      "end_time": 425202.0,
      "text": "Then I came to realize that after giving birth to four girls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 425226.0,
      "end_time": 428541.0,
      "text": "my mother had finally given birth to something"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 428565.0,
      "end_time": 432276.0,
      "text": "that could have made her be accepted into the community --"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 432300.0,
      "end_time": 433847.0,
      "text": "a baby boy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 433871.0,
      "end_time": 435450.0,
      "text": "my baby brother."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 436731.0,
      "end_time": 438718.0,
      "text": "But he, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 438742.0,
      "end_time": 441354.0,
      "text": "joined the list of the dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 443982.0,
      "end_time": 445891.0,
      "text": "The most hurting part for me"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 447409.0,
      "end_time": 451349.0,
      "text": "was the fact that I wasn't able to attend my mother's burial."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 451984.0,
      "end_time": 453270.0,
      "text": "I wasn't allowed."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 454654.0,
      "end_time": 459354.0,
      "text": "They said her family did not find it fit"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 459378.0,
      "end_time": 463162.0,
      "text": "for her children, who are all girls, to attend her burial,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 464160.0,
      "end_time": 465764.0,
      "text": "simply because we were girls."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 466806.0,
      "end_time": 468835.0,
      "text": "They would lament to me and say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 469634.0,
      "end_time": 471630.0,
      "text": "\"We are sorry, Mary, for your loss."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 472689.0,
      "end_time": 477848.0,
      "text": "We are sorry that your parents never left behind any children.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 479415.0,
      "end_time": 480850.0,
      "text": "And I would wonder:"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 481792.0,
      "end_time": 482976.0,
      "text": "What are we?"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 484610.0,
      "end_time": 485385.0,
      "text": "Are we not children?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 486858.0,
      "end_time": 489760.0,
      "text": "In the mentality of my community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 489784.0,
      "end_time": 491690.0,
      "text": "only the boy child counted."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 493419.0,
      "end_time": 496705.0,
      "text": "And for that reason, I knew this was the end of me."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 499606.0,
      "end_time": 501242.0,
      "text": "But I was the eldest girl."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 501794.0,
      "end_time": 503729.0,
      "text": "I had to take care of my siblings."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 503754.0,
      "end_time": 505790.0,
      "text": "I had to ensure they went to school."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 506674.0,
      "end_time": 509178.0,
      "text": "I was 13 years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 509745.0,
      "end_time": 512170.0,
      "text": "How could I have made that happen?"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 513207.0,
      "end_time": 516810.0,
      "text": "I came back to the camp to take care of my siblings."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 516835.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518390.00000000006,
      "text": "I've never felt so stuck."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 519799.0,
      "end_time": 524176.0,
      "text": "But then, one of my aunts, Auntie Okoi,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 524201.0,
      "end_time": 525990.0,
      "text": "decided to take my sisters."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 526643.0,
      "end_time": 529992.0,
      "text": "My father sent me money from Juba for me to go back to school."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 530829.0,
      "end_time": 534519.0,
      "text": "Boarding school was heaven, but it was also so hard."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 535154.0,
      "end_time": 538727.0,
      "text": "I remember during the visiting days when parents would come to school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 538751.0,
      "end_time": 540155.0,
      "text": "and my father would miss."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 540179.0,
      "end_time": 541889.0,
      "text": "But when he did come,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 541913.0,
      "end_time": 543700.0,
      "text": "he repeated the same faith in me."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 543724.0,
      "end_time": 545300.0,
      "text": "This time he would say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 545540.0,
      "end_time": 547762.0,
      "text": "\"Mary, you cannot go astray,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 547787.0,
      "end_time": 550989.0,
      "text": "because you are the future of your siblings.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 552142.0,
      "end_time": 555764.0,
      "text": "But then, in 2012,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 555788.0,
      "end_time": 559762.0,
      "text": "life took away the only thing that I was clinging on."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 560395.0,
      "end_time": 561721.0,
      "text": "My father died."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 563783.0,
      "end_time": 566190.0,
      "text": "My grades in school started to collapse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 567643.0,
      "end_time": 573624.0,
      "text": "and when I sat for my final high school exams in 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 573648.0,
      "end_time": 577240.0,
      "text": "I was devastated to receive a C grade."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 577264.0,
      "end_time": 579565.0,
      "text": "OK, I keep telling students in my class,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 579589.0,
      "end_time": 582958.0,
      "text": "\"It's not about the A's; it's about doing your best.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 583461.0,
      "end_time": 584640.0,
      "text": "That was not my best."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 585887.0,
      "end_time": 587151.0,
      "text": "I was determined."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 587176.0,
      "end_time": 589556.0,
      "text": "I wanted to go back and try again."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 590664.0,
      "end_time": 592295.0,
      "text": "But my parents were gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 592972.0,
      "end_time": 594526.0,
      "text": "I had no one to take care of me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 594551.0,
      "end_time": 596445.0,
      "text": "and I had no one to pay that fee."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 596863.0,
      "end_time": 598382.0,
      "text": "I felt so hopeless."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 600412.0,
      "end_time": 602562.0,
      "text": "But then, one of my best friends,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 602586.0,
      "end_time": 605939.0,
      "text": "a beautiful Kenyan lady, Esther Kaecha,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 605963.0,
      "end_time": 608260.0,
      "text": "called me during this devastating moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 608510.0,
      "end_time": 611412.0,
      "text": "and she was like, \"Mary, you have a strong will."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 611436.0,
      "end_time": 613685.0,
      "text": "And I have a plan, and it's going to work.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 614261.0,
      "end_time": 618257.0,
      "text": "OK, when you're in those devastating moments, you accept anything, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 618282.0,
      "end_time": 621393.0,
      "text": "So the plan was, she organized some travel money"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 621417.0,
      "end_time": 624528.0,
      "text": "for us to travel to Anester Victory Girls High School."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 625262.0,
      "end_time": 626693.0,
      "text": "I remember that day so well."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 626717.0,
      "end_time": 630174.0,
      "text": "It was raining when we entered the principal's office."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 630198.0,
      "end_time": 633294.0,
      "text": "We were shaking like two chickens that had been rained on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 633318.0,
      "end_time": 634492.0,
      "text": "and we looked at him."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 634516.0,
      "end_time": 636413.0,
      "text": "He was asking, \"What do you want?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 636890.0,
      "end_time": 639108.0,
      "text": "And we looked at him with the cat face."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 639132.0,
      "end_time": 641233.0,
      "text": "\"We just want to go back to school.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 641257.0,
      "end_time": 645596.0,
      "text": "Well, believe it or not, he not only paid our school fees"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 645620.0,
      "end_time": 649733.0,
      "text": "but also our uniform and pocket money for food."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 649757.0,
      "end_time": 650979.0,
      "text": "Clap for him."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 651400.0,
      "end_time": 652827.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 653766.0,
      "end_time": 655848.0,
      "text": "When I finished my high school career,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 655872.0,
      "end_time": 657405.0,
      "text": "I became the head girl."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 657984.0,
      "end_time": 661349.0,
      "text": "And when I sat for the KCSE for a second time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 661373.0,
      "end_time": 664230.0,
      "text": "I was able to receive a B minus. Clap."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 664470.0,
      "end_time": 666287.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 666311.0,
      "end_time": 667466.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 667490.0,
      "end_time": 671900.0,
      "text": "So I really want to say thank you to Anester Victory, Mr. Gatimu"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 671924.0,
      "end_time": 675607.0,
      "text": "and the whole Anester fraternity for giving me that chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 677840.0,
      "end_time": 678742.0,
      "text": "From time to time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 678767.0,
      "end_time": 683570.0,
      "text": "members of my family will insist that my sister and I should get married"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 683594.0,
      "end_time": 685692.0,
      "text": "so that somebody will take care of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 686722.0,
      "end_time": 688250.0,
      "text": "They will say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 688490.0,
      "end_time": 689396.0,
      "text": "\"We have a man for you.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 690153.0,
      "end_time": 695593.0,
      "text": "I really hate the fact that people took us as property rather than children."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 696920.0,
      "end_time": 698870.0,
      "text": "Sometimes they will jokingly say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 698111.0,
      "end_time": 700223.0,
      "text": "\"You are going to lose your market value"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 700247.0,
      "end_time": 701925.0,
      "text": "the more educated you become.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 702457.0,
      "end_time": 704439.0,
      "text": "But the truth is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 704463.0,
      "end_time": 707891.0,
      "text": "an educated woman is feared in my community."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 707916.0,
      "end_time": 709915.0,
      "text": "But I told them, this is not what I want."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 711560.0,
      "end_time": 714490.0,
      "text": "I don't want to get kids at 16 like my mother did."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 715494.0,
      "end_time": 717910.0,
      "text": "This is not my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 717528.0,
      "end_time": 719604.0,
      "text": "Even though my sisters and I are suffering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 719628.0,
      "end_time": 722156.0,
      "text": "there's no way we are heading in that direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 722528.0,
      "end_time": 724964.0,
      "text": "I refuse to repeat history."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 726940.0,
      "end_time": 731242.0,
      "text": "Educating a girl will create equal and stable societies."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 731266.0,
      "end_time": 735569.0,
      "text": "And educated refugees will be the hope"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 735593.0,
      "end_time": 738458.0,
      "text": "of rebuilding their countries someday."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 738956.0,
      "end_time": 742709.0,
      "text": "Girls and women have a part to play in this"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 742733.0,
      "end_time": 744554.0,
      "text": "just as much as men."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 744578.0,
      "end_time": 748259.0,
      "text": "Well, we have men in my family that encourage me to move on:"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 748283.0,
      "end_time": 751239.0,
      "text": "my half brothers and also my half sisters."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 752726.0,
      "end_time": 754644.0,
      "text": "When I finished my high school career,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 755285.0,
      "end_time": 760802.0,
      "text": "I moved my sisters to Nairobi, where they live with my stepsister."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 761411.0,
      "end_time": 763503.0,
      "text": "They live 17 people in a house."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 764138.0,
      "end_time": 765333.0,
      "text": "But don't pity us."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 765935.0,
      "end_time": 771363.0,
      "text": "The most important thing is that they all get a decent education."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 773534.0,
      "end_time": 775800.0,
      "text": "The winners of today"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 776900.0,
      "end_time": 777997.0,
      "text": "are the losers of yesterday,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 778557.0,
      "end_time": 780137.0,
      "text": "but who never gave up."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 780820.0,
      "end_time": 782709.0,
      "text": "And that is who we are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 782733.0,
      "end_time": 784126.0,
      "text": "my sisters and I."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 784150.0,
      "end_time": 786151.0,
      "text": "And I'm so proud of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 786175.0,
      "end_time": 787955.0,
      "text": "My biggest investment in life --"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 787980.0,
      "end_time": 789200.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 789440.0,
      "end_time": 791923.0,
      "text": "is the education of my sisters."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 792868.0,
      "end_time": 797536.0,
      "text": "Education creates an equal and fair chance for everyone to make it."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 798128.0,
      "end_time": 801419.0,
      "text": "I personally believe education is not all about the syllabus."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 801841.0,
      "end_time": 803188.0,
      "text": "It's about friendship."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 803746.0,
      "end_time": 805981.0,
      "text": "It's about discovering our talents."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 806500.0,
      "end_time": 809238.0,
      "text": "It's about discovering our destiny."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 809914.0,
      "end_time": 812468.0,
      "text": "I will, for example, not forget the joy that I had"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 812492.0,
      "end_time": 814730.0,
      "text": "when I first had singing lessons in school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 814754.0,
      "end_time": 816397.0,
      "text": "which is still a passion of mine."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 816421.0,
      "end_time": 818478.0,
      "text": "But I wouldn't have gotten that"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 818502.0,
      "end_time": 819758.0,
      "text": "anywhere else."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 821610.0,
      "end_time": 825468.0,
      "text": "As a teacher, I see my classroom as a laboratory"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 825492.0,
      "end_time": 828437.0,
      "text": "that not only generates skills and knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 828461.0,
      "end_time": 831315.0,
      "text": "but also understanding and hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 831881.0,
      "end_time": 833165.0,
      "text": "Let's take a tree."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 833894.0,
      "end_time": 835939.0,
      "text": "A tree may have its branches cut,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 837220.0,
      "end_time": 841451.0,
      "text": "but give it water, and it will grow new branches."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 841475.0,
      "end_time": 843780.0,
      "text": "For the child of war,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 843102.0,
      "end_time": 849129.0,
      "text": "an education can turn their tears of loss into a passion for peace."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 849153.0,
      "end_time": 854163.0,
      "text": "And for that reason, I refuse to give up on a single student in my class."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 854187.0,
      "end_time": 856503.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 856527.0,
      "end_time": 857969.0,
      "text": "Education heals."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 859790.0,
      "end_time": 861104.0,
      "text": "The school environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 861129.0,
      "end_time": 864170.0,
      "text": "gives you a focus to focus ahead."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 865245.0,
      "end_time": 866568.0,
      "text": "Let's take it this way:"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 866592.0,
      "end_time": 869550.0,
      "text": "when you're busy solving mathematical equations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 869790.0,
      "end_time": 871363.0,
      "text": "and you are memorizing poetry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 871388.0,
      "end_time": 875459.0,
      "text": "you forget the violence that you witnessed back home."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 875931.0,
      "end_time": 879416.0,
      "text": "And that is the power of education."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 879440.0,
      "end_time": 882290.0,
      "text": "It creates this place for peace."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 882856.0,
      "end_time": 884825.0,
      "text": "Kakuma is teeming with learners."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 884849.0,
      "end_time": 890260.0,
      "text": "Over 85,000 students are enrolled in schools here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 890500.0,
      "end_time": 893597.0,
      "text": "which makes up 40 percent of the refugee population."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 894400.0,
      "end_time": 900944.0,
      "text": "It includes children who lost years of education because of the war back home."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 901584.0,
      "end_time": 903478.0,
      "text": "And I want to ask you a question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 904568.0,
      "end_time": 908922.0,
      "text": "If education is about building a generation of hope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 909754.0,
      "end_time": 914398.0,
      "text": "why are there 120 students packed in my classroom?"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 916288.0,
      "end_time": 920307.0,
      "text": "Why is it that only six percent of the primary school students"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 920331.0,
      "end_time": 922670.0,
      "text": "are making it to high school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 922910.0,
      "end_time": 925754.0,
      "text": "simply because we do not have enough places for them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 926376.0,
      "end_time": 931435.0,
      "text": "And why is it that only one percent of the secondary school graduates"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 931459.0,
      "end_time": 933119.0,
      "text": "are making it to university?"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 934458.0,
      "end_time": 936833.0,
      "text": "I began by saying that I am a teacher."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 937692.0,
      "end_time": 941100.0,
      "text": "But once again, I have become a student."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 942247.0,
      "end_time": 944313.0,
      "text": "In March, I moved to Rwanda"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 945192.0,
      "end_time": 948775.0,
      "text": "on a scholarship program called \"Bridge2Rwanda.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 949503.0,
      "end_time": 952491.0,
      "text": "It prepares scholars for universities."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 953173.0,
      "end_time": 957523.0,
      "text": "They are able to get a chance to compete for universities abroad."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 957961.0,
      "end_time": 960772.0,
      "text": "I am now having teachers telling me what to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 960796.0,
      "end_time": 962845.0,
      "text": "instead of the other way round."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 962869.0,
      "end_time": 966507.0,
      "text": "People are once again investing in me."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 967587.0,
      "end_time": 972128.0,
      "text": "So I want to ask you all to invest in young refugees."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 972818.0,
      "end_time": 975930.0,
      "text": "Think of the tree that we mentioned earlier."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 975995.0,
      "end_time": 978659.0,
      "text": "We are the generation to plant it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 979422.0,
      "end_time": 982910.0,
      "text": "so that the next generation can water it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 983498.0,
      "end_time": 987594.0,
      "text": "and the one that follows will enjoy the shade."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 988360.0,
      "end_time": 990242.0,
      "text": "They will reap the benefits."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 991160.0,
      "end_time": 993457.0,
      "text": "And the greatest benefit of them all"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 994263.0,
      "end_time": 997482.0,
      "text": "is an education that will last."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 998840.0,
      "end_time": 999314.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 999648.0,
      "end_time": 1005751.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}